WEBVTT

00:02.107 --> 00:04.470
Okay, so he took you out to Watts. He showed me the 
condition and hired me, and it just was a miracle

00:04.530 --> 00:11.397
for me, because suddenly I have something to do. I 
can go out to clear slums,

00:12.638 --> 00:25.612
and put the zeal I would have put into the Methodist 
ministry into slum clearance. You can act on

00:25.692 --> 00:27.975
Christianity in a sound sound. Oh, absolutely. 
Monsignor O'Dwyer was really a practicing

00:30.575 --> 00:33.540
Christian. So was my father. But my father was 
ignorant. He didn't know the real world. O'Dwyer,

00:41.092 --> 00:46.381
through his charities, knew Los Angeles. Within 
three years, we had a housing authority

00:46.401 --> 00:49.506
established. We got the first projects built.

00:55.316 --> 00:57.139
And then the housing authority segregated them. 
one black, one brown, one white. This is 1942.

01:04.970 --> 01:13.042
There was no direction from the Supreme Court on 
the Constitutional question. That didn't come

01:13.062 --> 01:14.524
until 54. Even the Restrictive Covenant case 
didn't come down until 47. And O'Dwyer and I talked

01:21.613 --> 01:28.543
it over and felt it was just morally wrong for the 
projects to be segregated. And with the head of the

01:29.367 --> 01:44.822
League of Wimbledon, some liberal architects, 
and for the first time in our lives we set up a little

01:29.367 --> 01:44.822
picket line in front of the Housing Authority 
demanding that it integrate before it occupied.

01:46.424 --> 01:58.075
And within a few days the Housing Authority gave in 
and agreed and came out to the sidewalk where we

01:46.424 --> 01:58.075
were standing and in very mean words racist words, 
said they were going to integrate, and turned to

01:58.696 --> 02:07.484
O'Dwyer and said, who do you want to manage it? And 
O'Dwyer said, let's try Frank. So at the age of 28,

02:12.309 --> 02:25.902
from the picket line, I'm brought inside to become 
the manager of the first integrated housing

02:12.309 --> 02:25.902
project west of the Mississippi. And this whole 
thing that relates to the fact that it was that

02:29.864 --> 02:35.854
month, the first page, that we now have from the 
FBI. The first surveillance on me was a memorandum

02:37.337 --> 02:47.454
written by J. Edgar Hoover in 1942, deterring me to 
be a potential security risk. And from then on

02:48.135 --> 02:55.568
until 1980, everything in my life was 
orchestrated by the FBI, and I never knew it.

02:57.590 --> 02:59.493
That's a turning point in this whole thing. Maybe 
that's enough for you. No, I want to continue,

03:01.475 --> 03:04.119
unless you're too tired. I want to continue. I 
just... Do you want to take a break for a minute? No,

03:10.507 --> 03:11.328
I have the water. Okay. Would you... Times a 
quarter to three? I'd rather get it done with.

03:18.578 --> 03:21.903
Yeah, I'd like to... And rest my voice before I talk 
tonight. Yeah. Now, in Los Angeles, and in Watts,

03:24.168 --> 03:39.808
this Housing Council of Los Angeles, is this 
funded

03:24.168 --> 03:39.808
by public, private, or a combination of public and 
private funds? The Housing Council under

03:40.049 --> 03:44.054
Monsignor O'Dwyer was a private citizen group. 
Yeah, that's what I thought. The Housing

03:45.135 --> 03:50.662
Authority of the City of L.A. was set up by the 
federal government and state governments. It's a

03:50.823 --> 03:53.086
quasi-state corporation. Yeah. The funding came 
from the Wagner-Steagall Act of 1937,

03:54.222 --> 04:09.983
and from the Taft-Eleanor-Wagner

03:54.222 --> 04:09.983
bill of 1949. Let

04:11.725 --> 04:17.653
me just respond to questions. You wouldn't know 
any of this background, and you couldn't have

04:18.434 --> 04:24.162
questioned me on it, but now you know where I'm at. 
Yeah. You know the record a little bit from these

04:25.345 --> 04:28.069
other things. Yeah. Just let me respond to 
whatever you want. Okay, well, I want you to

04:30.271 --> 04:40.884
explain how well integrated housing and wants in 
World War II worked. What kind of problems did you

04:42.907 --> 04:44.188
have? It worked perfectly. We did not have 
problems. We... took people who had never had a

04:53.133 --> 05:06.608
flush toilet and gave them decent housing, and we 
completely overcame the argument that such

04:53.133 --> 05:06.608
people would turn the new housing into another 
slum. The projects were gardens, and we not only

05:07.529 --> 05:15.357
did good housing, but we did a lot of education. The 
Board of Education of L.A., for adult education

05:16.879 --> 05:22.785
for example, required an average daily 
attendance, I think, of twelve students, in order

05:23.761 --> 05:29.588
to justify a teacher. And I found out, when I'm 
managing these projects, that people would never

05:31.190 --> 05:46.109
come to a school or even the administration 
building for a class on, say, housekeeping,

05:31.190 --> 05:46.109
childcare. But the projects were built around 
central courtyards, where there'd be about

05:48.232 --> 05:53.278
sixteen families. And I got the Board of Education 
to allow a backyard, courtyard scene to be a

05:54.457 --> 06:01.947
classroom. And then all the mothers would come 
into a given kitchen to get a teaching lesson on

06:01.967 --> 06:10.158
cooking or sewing or whatnot. We became very, very 
much involved in basic education, political

06:11.740 --> 06:23.716
education.

06:23.736 --> 06:24.177
We I moved from the Ramona from the one project 
there in Watts. By the way, when the Watts

06:28.981 --> 06:31.144
Rebellion came in 65. I was going to ask you about 
that. The only place that didn't burn on 103rd

06:32.906 --> 06:37.071
Street was that project. That's interesting. 
There's a more complicated story in that, but I'll

06:39.494 --> 06:43.859
come back to it. I went up the ladder. I moved to the 
Ramona Gardens, which is a very, very much larger

06:46.322 --> 06:52.189
project. And I finally became assistant director 
of the Housing Authority in charge of the TAF

06:52.861 --> 07:04.116
program in 49, which gave us $110 million to spend. 
And I was given the job of selecting the sites and

07:04.216 --> 07:08.883
selling them to the city council. Yeah. At Ramona 
Gardens, where we had about a third Hispanic and a

07:10.805 --> 07:18.936
third black, we celebrated both Singletary Mile 
and Black History Week. This would be in the 40s,

07:26.850 --> 07:35.724
long before there was any sense of black or 
Hispanic consciousness and pride. We were doing

07:36.385 --> 07:38.368
it real, real early. I got Orson Welles and Rita 
Hayworth to come to Ramona Gardens to celebrate

07:39.169 --> 07:46.420
Singletary Mile. We had a Jewish and a Mexican and a 
black co-chair of Cinco de Mayo. And we tied it all

07:55.564 --> 08:05.581
together with the struggle against slavery in the 
States in the sixties. It was all combined

08:05.601 --> 08:08.826
educationally. The projects were beautifully 
maintained, and most of us in the work were

08:09.948 --> 08:16.699
committed. We had a zeal. It was not a nine-to-five 
job. I finally moved into the project because I

08:21.275 --> 08:26.680
didn't want to be an absentee. I wanted to live 
there at night. I wanted my kids to be brought up in

08:28.762 --> 08:33.666
the same place where I was asking other people to 
bring up their kids. So my kids were brought up in

08:34.186 --> 08:40.071
these projects in the old slum areas of L.A.

08:44.255 --> 08:46.737
The thing about the Watts jumps your way ahead.

08:49.703 --> 08:53.426
The influence we now know came from the FBI.

08:56.489 --> 09:04.397
They were very conscious of what was happening to 
me, and were beginning to maintain surveillance

08:56.489 --> 09:04.397
on me in the projects. We didn't know. We're 
getting the documents now. In 1952,

09:07.259 --> 09:16.588
without giving you all the circumstances, the FBI 
was able to get me fired from the Housing

09:17.243 --> 09:22.069
Authority. Yeah, we're going to talk about that. I 
want to talk about that. Let me just tell you the

09:24.532 --> 09:27.276
build-up on this thing. You see, civil liberties 
problems were bad in this country, especially

09:27.797 --> 09:45.259
from 45 to 49

09:27.797 --> 09:45.259
under Truman.

09:45.279 --> 09:45.900
But we had anti-communist oaths after the Smith 
Act of 1940. I have an absolutely lousy civil

09:51.668 --> 09:58.038
liberties record. I signed every loyalty oath 
they had. I swore I was not a communist. I each year

10:04.429 --> 10:12.141
took a special oath where we brought in the 
American Legion to stand with us with a battery of

10:04.429 --> 10:12.141
flags sign or oath that we would never overthrow 
the government by force and violence, whatever

10:13.184 --> 10:17.391
the oaths were. But by 1952, I had gone through 
changes. I'd watched the Un-American Activities

10:23.521 --> 10:39.367
Committee destroy the motion picture people in 
LA, and school teachers, and some knowledge I had

10:23.521 --> 10:39.367
of labor, and I was getting more and more critical 
of this idea. And I also was ready to regurgitate,

10:41.602 --> 10:44.326
literally. But once a year I suddenly have to prove 
I'm loyal by taking an oath and bringing in the L.A.

10:45.348 --> 10:59.329
Times to take a picture of me, signing, putting up 
my hand with the Legionnaires with their funny

10:45.348 --> 10:59.329
little hats. And I

10:59.349 --> 11:08.503
was in an eminent domain for seniors where the FBI 
did it. I was in an eminent domain proceeding on the

11:09.614 --> 11:25.675
necessity of taking Chavez Ravine, which is today 
the Dodger Ballpark, as the site for the larger

11:09.614 --> 11:25.675
project on the new ten thousand units that we were 
building. Thirty-five hundred units. It was

11:29.781 --> 11:38.052
designed by an architect friend that I live with, 
Richard Neutra, the most modern, designed to make

11:38.622 --> 11:46.051
it beautiful in those hills above L.A. And I was the 
expert. I knew all the correlations between bad

11:46.171 --> 12:02.229
housing and disease and delinquency, 
communicable disease, crime, the arguments you

11:46.171 --> 12:02.229
need to prove the necessity of taking private 
property for public use. And I'd been through ten

12:03.451 --> 12:07.195
trials in L.A. We won them all. And I was in one in 
August of 52.

12:15.343 --> 12:23.633
I'd been on the stand for a day of direct and then a 
day of cross-examination. And I knew every block.

12:27.557 --> 12:29.259
I knew the statistic. I was really professionally 
qualified to do what I was doing. Suddenly the real

12:33.444 --> 12:35.747
estate lawyers, owners, who were trying to block 
our access. They didn't want it taken because they

12:40.551 --> 12:50.764
did not want minorities brought into that part of 
L.A. And the restrictive covenant ruling ended up

12:40.551 --> 12:50.764
only coming down in 1947. And they called public 
housing socialized housing, creeping

12:52.066 --> 12:59.255
socialism, even though Senator Taft was the 
author. All kinds of reasons. And they were

13:03.020 --> 13:06.004
speculating on the land. to turn it into luxury 
apartments. And suddenly, in an ever-demanding

13:10.974 --> 13:18.700
proceeding, you've got to understand, hours, 
this block, that block, how do you know that? Where

13:19.200 --> 13:23.684
do you get your information on rat infestation and 
so on? They suddenly say, now, Mr. Wilkinson,

13:24.045 --> 13:36.615
would you please

13:24.045 --> 13:36.615
tell us all organizations, political or 
otherwise, that you belonged to since 1931?

13:39.317 --> 13:48.108
Totally

13:39.317 --> 13:48.108
irrelevant, immaterial question, except that 
was the summer of 1952. The Korean War was then in

13:48.188 --> 13:52.854
its second year.

13:55.917 --> 13:57.359
The Hollywood Ten were in jail. Alger Hiss was a bad 
guy. The Rosenbergs were due to be executed the

14:00.603 --> 14:03.226
following year. Red hysteria. Really hysteria. 
And my lawyer had been a radical, or more radical,

14:06.953 --> 14:16.567
back at UCLA days. In the 30s, probably. And now had 
become a Republican. And the Housing Authority,

14:20.633 --> 14:27.824
to protect itself, had hired all Republican law 
firms to represent us in the eminent domain

14:20.633 --> 14:27.824
proceeding. So when the question came, he could 
only think of me as he knew me. We'd never had any

14:32.811 --> 14:35.475
conversation about what had happened to me since. 
And so he thought to challenge the question on

14:37.379 --> 14:46.152
relevancy would be bad public relations. So he 
allowed me to answer. And I qualified myself as an

14:47.354 --> 14:55.446
expert witness, where I trained professional 
societies I belonged to. But then they pressed me,

14:55.486 --> 15:04.600
and now the political organizations, they didn't 
ask me, are you a communist? The political

15:04.920 --> 15:06.863
organizations And at that point, for the first 
time I reached that point, I said, I won't answer.

15:16.397 --> 15:18.799
And then my lawyer objected. And then the judge 
turned to the lawyer and said his objection was not

15:19.880 --> 15:24.744
timely. And he turned to me and he said, I think you 
need a lawyer. And I was suspended.

15:32.871 --> 15:37.575
And suddenly all hell broke loose in L.A. because 
we now know that J. Edgar Hoover, working with our

15:38.753 --> 15:52.465
chief of police, Parker, and with real estate 
interests, they were all working with Parker, had

15:38.753 --> 15:52.465
developed a dossier on me. We never knew this. And 
the dossier had been floating around town, and no

15:55.168 --> 15:58.811
one would touch it. It went to our Republican 
mayor, and I was working with him around the clock.

16:05.377 --> 16:08.440
I was five days on one telethon in the Chamber of 
Commerce building with the mayor. And they gave

16:13.589 --> 16:15.231
him this dossier. The chief went in to see him. And 
he looked at it and tore it up and said, I know this

16:17.533 --> 16:25.600
boy and I trust him. Get out of here. A year after I 
was suspended, Fletcher Bowen, this wonderful

16:29.804 --> 16:38.292
Republican mayor who I'd known as a child in my home 
My father, you know, my father helped to elect him,

16:38.626 --> 17:08.363
part of a reform against the prostitution and the 
gambling interests of L.A.

16:38.626 --> 17:08.363
Two nights before his election in 1953, Chief 
Parker, on television, with a member of the

16:38.626 --> 17:08.363
Un-American Activities Committee, Washington, 
came in and on television they said, now tell us

16:38.626 --> 17:08.363
about the relationship between Frank Wilkinson 
and the mayor, and all this public knowledge was

17:08.782 --> 17:10.745
brought out. And then the dossier was brought out. 
The first time I ever knew there was a dossier was

17:13.129 --> 17:18.457
nine months after it had been used. And it was read 
on television. I heard my dossier the first time

17:20.900 --> 17:23.825
read on television. It was ridiculous stuff. 
Today we laugh at it, but then it was scary. Tell me

17:31.116 --> 17:32.578
some of the stuff. I've been seen talking to a 
communist at the corner of 4th and Spring Street in

17:34.735 --> 17:45.529
Los Angeles that I had subscribed to the People's 
World newspaper.

17:48.753 --> 17:50.215
Yeah. All right. Was any of it true? I don't know 
about the communists at 4th and Spring Street. I

17:57.225 --> 17:59.107
would think it probably was true. And the 
subscription to the People's World, yes, it was

18:00.189 --> 18:04.354
true. I subscribed to everything. Yeah, so what? 
So what? At any rate, this was read, and then Chief

18:11.053 --> 18:21.103
Parker— In that, were you called a—did it say that 
you were a member of the communist power? Nothing

18:21.423 --> 18:31.252
in there said that I was a—the dossier didn't in any 
way suggest I had any communist connections. I

18:31.352 --> 18:32.974
just associated with the paper and people who were 
communists. See, in the 1940s, communists were

18:35.987 --> 18:39.693
people. They ran for office. They were even part of 
our housing council. All right. They then

18:50.571 --> 18:59.265
described, Parker described how he took it to 
Bowron, and Bowron tore it up and threw it in the

18:50.571 --> 18:59.265
wastebasket and told him to get out of his office. 
and this is all hammed up by the un-American guy.

19:03.529 --> 19:07.334
And they said, really, really, really? That's the 
man who's running for mayor tomorrow? All right,

19:11.499 --> 19:15.564
the election, Bowron would have gone in with 80%. 
He had a perfect record. He got something like 36%

19:17.646 --> 19:20.209
of the vote. And the new mayor came in, and within 
two weeks, turned over Chavez Ravine, where we had

19:20.750 --> 19:29.100
spent $7 million acquiring it. in developing it, 
turned it over to Walter O'Malley and the Brooklyn

19:30.380 --> 19:36.647
Dodgers for a ballpark for four million. One

19:36.667 --> 19:43.114
final point here that we'd forget if you just 
questioned me. One thing about how I did get

19:43.314 --> 19:47.779
connected with the Un-American Activities 
Committee. Yeah, we have to talk about that. My

19:50.222 --> 19:58.311
connection with that was entirely

19:50.222 --> 19:58.311
an accident.

